Also, avoid using `setPreferredSize`, let the layout managers do their job.  In the example I&#39;m used `insets` (from `GridBagConstraints`) and an `EmptyBorder` to add some additional space around the components

Also, be careful of using AWT components (ie `Choice`), they don&#39;t always play nicely with Swing.  In this case, you should be using `JComboBox`


