It seems that the algorithm should be reconsidered just to move the lower elements _before_ the _head_ element starting at position 0:
* if current element is less than head, _rotate_ all elements from `head` to current position to the right by 1.

Example implementation:
```java
static void arrange(int[] arr) {
    int head = 0;
    for (int i = head + 1; i &lt; arr.length; i++) {
        if (arr[i] &lt; arr[head]) {
            rotate(arr, head, i);
            head++;
        }
    }
}

static void rotate(int[] arr, int head, int i) {
    int tmp = arr[i];
    for (int j = i; j &gt; head; j--) {
        arr[j] = arr[j - 1];
    }
    arr[head] = tmp;
}
```
